	<term>implicit focus</term>
	<definition><p>A mode in which the window under the <glossary tag="mouse pointer">mouse pointer</glossary> is the <glossary tag="active window">active window</glossary> and receives all typed characters, even if that window is not frontmost.</p>
<p></p>
<p>Also called &quot;pointer focus&quot; and &quot;sloppy focus&quot;.</p></definition>
	<categories>
	 	<category>Windows &amp; Dialog Boxes</category>
	</categories>
	<synonyms>
	 	<synonym>pointer focus</synonym>
	 	<synonym>implicit focus</synonym>
	</synonyms>
